        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 1:42PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 142 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Simla, or 26 miles west of Limon, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Simla and Matheson.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
